            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hi, I'm trying to work on this issue.\n\n1. `dd` uses [`extmark_adjust`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/extmark.c#L478) to adjust the position of extmarks, which in turn calls on\\_bytes with the wrong parameter\n\n   The position calculation doesn't cover the case when the entire buffer is deleted. To fix this I need to get the length of the last line in buffer, but I can't do that since the function is only called after the deletion happened. So it's difficult to fix without changing that behavior.\n2. After working on this a bit, I am somewhat convinced that those positions are fine\n  - Position being out of bound is fine, as  this happens every time when the last line is deleted\n  - They result in the same state, because using `dd` on a single line is basically deleting the line first and then inserting a new line, which is what the parameters are trying to say.\n\n",
