            "body": "> Position being out of bound is fine, as this happens every time when the last line is deleted\n\nThat means the bug is reproducible, not that the current behavior is fine.\n\n> using dd on a single line is basically deleting the line first and then inserting a new line\n\nSure, but the old end position should still be within bounds. And I assume the new line being \"inserted\" would be empty, so shouldn't we expect the new end position to be the same as the start position?",
