            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I agree that `new_end` should be `{row = 0, col = 0, byte_len = 0}`. \n\nHowever I still have some doubt on the correct positions. Consider this example\n\n```\n1 | line\n2 | line\n3 | line\n4 | line\n5 | line\n    ^\n    cursor\n```\n\nThese are the positions when I press `dd`\n\n```\nstart_pos: {\n  byte_len = 20,\n  col = 0,\n  row = 4\n}\nold_pos: {\n  byte_len = 5,\n  col = 0,\n  row = 1\n}\nnew_pos: {\n  byte_len = 0,\n  col = 0,\n  row = 0\n}\n```\n\nWe can see that `old_pos` is out of bound. \n\nIf we try to move `old_pos` in bound, then we probably can't differentiate between `dd` and `cc`, in the sense that one has the final line count of 4 while the other has 5.\n\nMaybe the correct thing to do for `dd` in this case is to move `start_pos` to the end of the previous line? That makes sense to me but I think I'll wait for someone to confirm the correct behavior",
